# ==============================================================================
# 09. scFEA flux post-processing and visualization across multiple analyses
#
# Description:
# This script imports per-cell metabolic-flux matrices generated by scFEA and
# processes one or more analyses defined in an external manifest. For each
# analysis, it:
#
#   1. matches scFEA cell barcodes to Seurat metadata;
#   2. calculates mean flux for each configured cell state;
#   3. optionally calculates biological-sample-level mean flux;
#   4. removes modules with zero or undefined variance across cell states;
#   5. applies reviewed cell-state and metabolic-module orders;
#   6. exports full and selected-module flux matrices;
#   7. generates full and selected-module heatmaps;
#   8. saves a compact RDS bundle and analysis parameters.
#
# Important:
# This script does not run the scFEA model. The exact scFEA command, model
# version, input expression matrix, and model files used to generate the flux
# matrix should be archived separately.
#
# Statistical note:
# Cell-state means are used for descriptive heatmaps. They must not be treated
# as independent biological replicates for inferential statistics. When a valid
# biological-sample column is supplied, sample-level summaries are also exported.
#
# Author:
# Jinjin Zhu
#
# Configuration:
#   config/scFEA/09_scFEA_manifest.csv
#
# Main outputs:
#   DATA/OUTPUT/scFEA/
#   TABLE/scFEA/<analysis_id>/
#   FIGURE/scFEA/<analysis_id>/
# ==============================================================================


# 1. Load packages -------------------------------------------------------------

